StoryAsset.name: New League Match Up User Lower

keyValuePair.Value: You must be delighted with that win?
What a great day for %1s, beating the league leaders. What did you make of your team's performance? Can you push on from here?
We were ready for a tough game.

They've got so many dangerous attacking players ,so we always knew we'd be in for a tough game. But the lads were up for it, weren't they? It was a very solid display. Being in control defensively gave us the confidence to go and play a bit ourselves. I'm delighted. That's a very good three points.
That's what this team's capable of.

The boys were excellent today. We put the opposition's defence under pressure all game and took our opportunities. Maybe the players surprised themselves a bit. Well, I know what they're capable of and everybody saw it today. Now I want them to play like that every week!
Great win. Enjoy it. And move on.

We did everything right today. I couldn't have asked for more from my team. It was a big win. They can enjoy themselves tonight and then back into training to get ready for the next challenge. We have to build on this.
What a great win. How important was that?
That’s a big win for %1s, beating the league leaders. You must be delighted. How did your team pull it off?
They couldn't handle our attacking play at all.

The boys were sensational going forward today. Up against really well-organised team, we just never gave them a moment's peace. And in the end the pressure told. I'm really pleased for the players. We got the win we definitely deserved.
We made ourselves difficult to play against the whole game.

We knew we'd be up against very good players. But that was the best I've seen from us defensively for ages. We closed down spaces, got our tackles and blocks in and then, when we had the ball, we used it really intelligently. To do all that today was great. Now I want us at that level every week.
Happy days!

I couldn't be happier with my team. We were better all over the pitch and definitely deserved the win. That sets our standard now. Let's enjoy today and then get our heads down in training to prepare for the next game.
What can you learn from that defeat?
%1s are a very good side and that's why they're top of the league. But you must have expected your boys to have a chance of beating them. What went wrong?
We let ourselves down in the big moments.

We had some good spells in the game and caused them problems. But all our good work was undone by some very basic errors at big moments in the game. I know we were up against a very good team but I expect more from these players: more determination, better concentration. I hate to lose the way we did.
We looked dangerous going forward.

I thought we gave them problems the whole game whenever we attacked. We were clever and the work-rate was excellent. But it wasn't enough. It's a pity. When you try to take a game to the opposition like we did, it's tough not to come out of it with some kind of result.
We know where we have to improve.

There's a reason %1s are top of the league. They have very good players. But my boys competed well today. We won't feel sorry for ourselves about the defeat. We'll learn our lessons and make sure we improve.
Is the draw a decent result for you?
How do you see today's draw? You've kept the league leaders in reach? Or you've missed a chance to gain ground?
We had a real opportunity today.

I can't fault the players for effort. We set out to win and we had control of things for spells in the game. What we didn't do, though, was create enough chances. A bit more quality, a little more self-belief. That's where we need to improve.
We can't go into games scared of the opposition.

I thought we could have got a win today but the players looked a bit short on self-belief. To get the better of good sides, you have to be mentally strong. Play the team in front of you, not their reputation. I don't think our lads ever really thought they could beat the league leaders.
We gave them a game, at least.

We were playing the best in the league and I thought our lads really stepped up to the challenge. There were chances at both ends. I was very pleased with how our boys held firm even when we were under pressure. I think the leaders will be happy to have got out with a draw today.
Did you miss an opportunity today?

That was a game that could have gone either way. You must be pleased that, against the league leaders, you didn't look out of your depth. In fact, do you think you missed a great opportunity to record a famous win?
We just didn't create enough chances.

I thought we really gave their defence problems today. Nobody could have complained if one more chance had fallen our way and we'd nicked a win. Maybe the lads will believe a bit more in themselves now. I genuinely believe we're good enough to challenge the best.
We have to better-organised defensively.

I thought you saw us give the league leaders a real game out there. I know they've got excellent attacking players but I expected us to be able to handle them. Unfortunately, we let ourselves down with some avoidable errors today. Maybe nerves got the better of one or two of our lads.
Our midfield is a match for anyone.

You could say we never really controlled midfield. But I don't think the league leaders did either. That's credit to our lads in there who proved that, when it comes to energy and effort, they're a match for anyone.
How do you explain that defeat?
%1s are a good team but you must be disappointed not to have taken something from the game. Why do you think your boys ended up losing?
We need to be more careful with the ball.

I can't fault the lads for effort but we spent a lot of time chasing around the pitch having to win the ball back. We have to take more care in possession. We were competitive out there but did we create enough chances? We need to improve our decision-making, that's for sure.
The players will have found out a bit about themselves today.

The boys went into today's match knowing they were up against the very best. Credit to them, they never gave way. We lost but I think we gave as good as good as we got for almost the whole of the 90 minutes. I'd say we deserved to get something from the game.
We probably didn't make enough chances.

We were playing a very good %1s team. They've got top players all over the pitch. Maybe we shouldn't be surprised that we struggled to make any impression. We never looked like getting on top. That's the level we're competing at, so let's do everything we can to improve.
That was an incredible victory. How did it happen?
A bit of history for your team today, beating the league leaders. I think nobody expected it. You must be delighted. How did the boys get the better of such a good team?
We fought for every 50/50.

I thought we put in committed performances all over the pitch today. We made it difficult for the opposition to get into any kind of rhythm and then, when we had the ball, we were brave. The boys deserved the win and I hope that's the level we can reach in every game now.
We knew we could get something out of the game.

The lads knew they'd have to be at their very best to get anything out of a team that's so strong defensively. But they always believed they could do something special. They believed in themselves and that won us the game. The lads were incredible.
We knew how important this game was.

I've always known we had good players. I believe in this team. Everything came together for us today. The lads were strong, aggressive, organised and brave enough to go and grab a great win. It was an important performance. I hope we've proved what we're capable of now.

I've always known we had good players. I believe in this team. Everything came together for us today. The lads were strong, aggressive, organised and brave enough to go and grab a great win. It was an important performance. I hope we've proved what we're capable of now.
You must be satisfied with a draw today?
You must be satisfied with a draw today?
It's been tough for your boys lately. So a draw against the league leaders looks like a very good result. Are you pleased? Or do you think you might even have snatched a win?
It's been tough for your boys lately. So a draw against the league leaders looks like a very good result. Are you pleased? Or do you think you might even have snatched a win?
We stood up strong.

They're the league leaders for a reason! The lads prepared really well for the game and fought for every inch out there. I have to be happy for them and I hope they've proved to themselves now that they can compete against the best. The next step is to go on and win games like that one.
We could have grabbed the win there, you know.

The players were up against very good opponents today. Everybody worked together, worked hard for the team. But I'm a disappointed, to be honest. If we'd been a bit braver in the big moments, I think we could have won today. The lads will know they've missed out on doing something special here.
I have to be happy with a draw.

Looking at the game, you wouldn't say we looked out of our depth against the best in the league. It could have gone either way but I think we proved today we can be competitive against even the best teams. We definitely deserved the draw.
It was always going to be tough, wasn't it?
A game against the league leaders was always going to be a big ask for your team. What can you take from the defeat? Were there any positives for you?
We gave it a go today.

The lads were up against some of the best players. It was a frustrating afternoon for us. We struggled to create chances. We have to move on from this. I'm looking for leaders in that dressing room now. We have to use today as motivation to improve.
I think we went into it expecting the worst.

It's hard against a very good team but players have to believe in themselves. Today we just looked shell-shocked, as if we expected the opposition to roll over us and score their goals. We made it too easy for them. We lost the psychological battle before we'd even kicked off.
We've been taught a bit of a lesson there.

The lads gave it everything. They chased and got their tackles in. But they were up against the best around and it was only a matter of time before we started to suffer in the game. They'll learn, though. And now they know the level we have to aim for. I'm sure this team can grow.
That was an incredible win. Did you see it coming?
Up against the league leaders today, I don't think anybody gave your boys a chance. But you turned in an incredible performance and pulled off a famous win. How did you do it?
Maybe we proved a few people wrong.

The boys have taken a lot of criticism recently, so I was really pleased for them today. This was a big game and they met the challenge head-on. They proved how good they can be. Up against very good opponents, we were always ready to plug dangerous gaps and make the big tackles. Let's push on from this now.
That was outstanding from the boys.

Games are won and lost in midfield, we know that. My boys were sensational today. We won every 50/50, tracked their runners and then tried to make things happen when we had the ball. Individually and collectively, the players did everything I could have asked from them.
It was always going to need a big performance today.

I was very pleased with how decisive we were in the final third. The lads did a fantastic job. We knew we wouldn't see much of the ball but we kept the pressure on the opposition, chased lost causes and tried to make things happen. Most important, we didn't waste a single chance that came our way.

I was very pleased with how decisive we were in the final third. The lads did a fantastic job. We knew we wouldn't see much of the ball but we kept the pressure on the opposition, chased lost causes and tried to make things happen. Most important, we didn't waste a single chance that came our way.
Would it be fair to say you're satisfied with a draw?
Would it be fair to say you're satisfied with a draw?

If you look at the table, it seemed a bit of a mis-match for you, up against the league leaders. But your boys managed to come away with a draw. You must be pleased. Did the game go according to plan?

If you look at the table, it seemed a bit of a mis-match for you, up against the league leaders. But your boys managed to come away with a draw. You must be pleased. Did the game go according to plan?
We proved we can compete.

I think people expected us to get overrun here. But my boys proved a few doubters wrong today. I can't fault them for work-rate and for attitude. They really tried to go toe to toe against some very good players. They've set a standard for themselves now. Play like that every week and we'll definitely win more than we lose.
I think that's a game we should have won.

Of course I'm happy with a draw. It's a good result against a very good team. But I really think that, if the lads had backed themselves a little more and been a bit braver, we could have turned the draw into a win today. The game was there for us. We should have had the courage to go and grab our chance
I'm happy we kept such a good shape.

The league leaders are great going forward so it was important we stayed solid this afternoon. Well done to the boys is all I can say. Everyone followed instructions and did their jobs. We made ourselves difficult to play through. A draw's a good result. I'm a very happy man.
That went with the form book. Could you have avoided defeat?
Playing the league leaders, everyone probably expected you to lose. So the result's no surprise but do you think your team missed an opportunity today?
We did our best. Now we have to improve.

I can't criticise the effort my players put into the game. But, against the best teams, working hard isn't always enough. You can be caught out at any moment. The boys will have to focus on the good things they did and aim to cut out the mistakes which let us down today.
We just switched off too often.

Against the good teams, you can't relax. Anywhere on the pitch, you can't afford to lose your man for a moment or good players will find a way to hurt you. That's what happened today. I think the lads will have to look at themselves after this. Did we do enough? I don't think so.
That was very hard work out there.

We didn't have much of the ball today so it was always going to be difficult for us to get men forward and create scoring opportunities. The lads worked hard enough but we didn't really make things happen when we were in possession. Maybe we were just beaten by a better team.
A tight game. You must be pleased to have come out on top?
You went into the game knowing a win could get you closer to the second-placed team in the league. So that was a big victory. Did things turn out the way you'd expected?
We made big decisions in the key moments.

We always expected this would be a close game. On days like today you need something special from your players. You need a bit of magic, or someone making the right decision at a key moment. The boys didn't disappoint us, did they? They were excellent. We fully deserved the win.
We didn't shirk the battle out there.

I look at a game and I see one-on-one battles all over the pitch. Today, every one of our players won his. That's what gave us the level of control we needed to go on and win the game. I hope the lads will look at what they did out there, individually and collectively, and make that the level we aim at in every match now.
Let's enjoy the win and then prepare properly for next week.

The team as a whole played at the level I expect from them. I'm happy with the players, of course. I was confident we could win today. Now we need to get our heads down and make sure we're ready for our next game.
Did your team miss an opportunity today?
A draw's not a bad result. It means you stay within touching distance. But do you think your players missed the chance to claim all three points and close the gap today?
There's more to come from these players.

The players did a lot of good things in the game today, especially when it came to stopping the other team playing. I'm grateful for all their hard work. But I think this group is capable of more. A little more intelligence when we were in possession and I think we could have ended up with the win.
We let ourselves down a bit today.

I really thought we could win today and close the gap to second-place. So I was really disappointed we couldn't stay solid and see the game out. You can have a plan but that doesn't count for anything when players make individual mistakes. We've missed out there, for sure.
The lads gave us pretty much everything we asked for.

It was always going to be tight today and I can't be unhappy with the draw. The lads prepared well this week. Everybody did his job out there and I'm happy enough with them. It's just you can't help but think that, if we'd created one more good chance, I could have been stood here now and celebrating a win.
A disappointing defeat. What went wrong?
Today was an opportunity to make up ground on %1s in the table but you lost the game. How disappointed are you and what went wrong for your team?
You have to take your chances, don't you?

When you lose a game but your team has given everything, you can't be too disappointed. But today we could have got at least a draw. When you create goal-scoring opportunities but don't take them, it always puts you under pressure. That's why we lost and it's frustrating.
The lads ran their hearts out.

The boys worked very hard out there. This was always looked a difficult fixture for us because the opposition have excellent players all through their line-up. But we competed well. We created some goal-scoring opportunities, too. But we didn't take them and that's what probably cost us our chance in the game.
We kept calm under pressure.

I was pleased with the character shown by my players today. It was a tight game and there weren't that many efforts on goal, so credit to our boys for that. We lost because we didn't take our chances but %1s were decisive when it really mattered. That explains the result.
In a game with so much at stake, were you pleased with your team's display.
There was a lot at stake today, a game between two high-flying teams. Your boys managed to get the better of things. Were you pleased with the %1s performance? What was it that gave you the edge?
We kept it tight.

It was a very close game against a good team. It was important that we maintained our discipline defensively. I thought our lads managed to keep the opposition at arm's length for most of the game. That gave us the initiative and we were able to go on and win.
We took our chances. Well done, boys!

That's exactly the kind of attacking football I want to see from my team in every game. We kept the opposition under pressure, created chances and scored when it mattered. We were well worth the win. I won't accept anything less from the lads from now on!
It was a solid team performance.

The defence was solid. We were creative up front. And we competed for 90 minutes in midfield. It was a good team performance and we got the result we deserved. Let's prepare properly and turn in another good display in our next game.
Very little between the teams. Could you have won today?
You have set very high standards for your %1s team. In a close game today, you had to settle for a draw. Are you happy with the result? And how about the performance?
We need to take charge of games like that.

In a game like today, it's important to control possession as much as you can. We did that effectively for long spells in the game, so I'm disappointed we didn't win. Maybe we just need to look at being a bit more creative when we have the chance to go forward. Let's be brave with the ball.
We know we made mistakes out there.

The boys had good control for a lot of the game today. We knew we'd have to look after possession properly if we were to going to get the win against a very good team. We were let down by individual errors, though. Those moments you can't prepare for. The players have to take responsibility themselves.
It just didn't run for us.

I'm very happy with the energy and commitment shown by my players today. In such a tight game, though, between two good teams, you need a little luck to turn a draw into a win. The ball never seemed to run for our boys in the final third. One clear-cut chance was probably all we needed.
That could prove a costly defeat. What did you make of the game?
You knew beforehand that %1s would give you as tough game. On the day, they were probably the better side. What went wrong for your team? Could you have set the team up differently to avoid defeat?
We have to look after the ball better.

I don't think there was anything wrong with how we set up for the game. On days like this, you have to make possession count and our lads struggled to do that. There were so many misplaced passes out there. When we should have been creating chances, too often we just put pressure on ourselves.
We were up against a well-organised team.

The lads did their best in their individual battles. Well done to them for that. They chased and put pressure on their opposite numbers. The problem was that we didn't really into any kind of rhythm. We won't score unless we create decent opportunities. That was the story of it from our point of view.
We were put under plenty of pressure.

I'm not here to criticise any individual player. They all competed well against very dangerous opponents. The problem was that we gave the ball away too often. We have to be more demanding of each other and communicate better. Until we do that, we'll struggle against teams as good as %1s.
A surprise victory for you. How did you manage it?

It's safe to say that a lot of people were surprised to see you come out on top today, against a team flying high in the table. What was your game plan? How pleased were you with your players' display?
It was a good day for us, I'd say.

Our creative players made all the difference today. You need good decision-making and a bit of technical quality to decide a game like that one. I'm really pleased with the whole team. But now I want to see that level of performance from them in every single game.
Great work defensively today.

That was as good a display when we were out of possession as I've seen from the boys in quite a while. I think we all did our jobs. We looked hungry to win the ball back and then looked to find space to give ourselves options when we attacked. We dominated the game and were well worth the win, in my opinion.
The team showed what they're capable of.

We really needed the win today. I think the team knew that. In that situation, sometimes players feel the pressure. I think you saw, though, that my lads rose to the occasion here. Absolutely we deserved the victory.
Happy to have taken a draw today?
Happy to have taken a draw today?
You knew today's opponents were in very good form. It was a real challenge for your team. But you managed to take a draw from the game. Were you pleased with the attitude you saw from your players?
You knew today's opponents were in very good form. It was a real challenge for your team. But you managed to take a draw from the game. Were you pleased with the attitude you saw from your players?
It could have been easy for us to fold.

They have such good players all over the pitch. I think people expected our lads would struggle to contain them. But, instead, we rose to the occasion. A great level of commitment and plenty of bravery on the ball. I hope the players have set a standard they can match in every game now.
We definitely had the chances to win today.

Did we doubt ourselves a bit today? I'm not sure the players really believed we could get the better of the opposition here. The lads all did their jobs but I think if we'd been a little braver and more imaginative in the final third, we could definitely have turned a draw into something better.
We fought hard for that today.

Today was a chance for our lads to measure themselves against some of the best players in the league. I thought the team battle hard to get something from the game. It was a mature performance, in my opinion. Certainly a draw was the very least we deserved.
Was today's defeat a foregone conclusion?
Your opponents are going so well in the league and are way above you in the table. Was this a game that you were almost expecting to lose? Or were you expecting more from your team?
We made chances, didn't we?

The players will be disappointed to lose the game, of course. It's a blow. But I want the lads to take some positives from today. They worked hard and they made chances against a good team. If we can do this in future matches, we'll get some wins, for sure.
We made it too easy for them to get behind us.

We can work hard all week in training and set out a game plan. But if we don't work together effectively as a defensive unit when it comes to the match, then we make it too easy for opponents to get in behind us. That's what happened today. We have to be more disciplined as a team.
Look, they were probably better than us.

We've got good, honest players in our team. You won't ever see any of my lads letting us down in terms of work-rate and endeavour. But you just have to say that we were up against a better side today and never got any kind of control of the game. We always looked second-best.
